findings.suggestion:
BEFORE:
const clamped = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, score))

AFTER:
function clampScore(score: number): number {
  return Math.max(0, Math.min(100, score))
}
// Then use: const clamped = clampScore(score)

WHY: A named helper makes the domain intent (score is clamped to 0-100) immediately clear without parsing nested Math calls. Also centralizes the range constants if they ever change. Note: only 2 occurrences, so this is a minor suggestion per the project's 'three similar lines > premature abstraction' guideline.

